column1: This model requires log backups. Work is not lost due to a lost or damaged data file. Data can be recovered to an arbitrary point in time (for example, prior to an error). Normally, there is no work loss exposure. If the end of the log is damaged, changes since the most recent log backup must be redone. With this model, you can recover to a specific point in time, assuming that your backups are complete up to that point in time. Note: If you have two or more full-recovery-model databases that must be logically consistent, you may have to implement special procedures to ensure the recoverability of these databases.
column2: 此模型需要日志备份。由于数据文件丢失或损坏，工作不会丢失。可以将数据恢复到任意时间点（例如，在发生错误之前）。通常，没有工作损失的风险。如果日志末尾已损坏，则必须重做自最近一次日志备份以来的更改。使用此模型，假设备份在该时间点之前已完成，则可以恢复到特定时间点。注意：如果您有两个或多个在逻辑上必须一致的完全恢复模型数据库，则可能必须实施特殊过程以确保这些数据库的可恢复性。

column1: This database has been changed by a User and set to the EMERGENCY state. Currently, the database is in single-user mode and may be repaired or restored. In this state, the database is marked as READ_ONLY. Logging is disabled and access is limited to members of the sysadmin fixed server role. The EMERGENCY state is mainly used for troubleshooting purposes. For example, a database marked as suspect can be set to the EMERGENCY state. This could allow the system administrator read-only access to the database. <b>Note:<b/> Only members of the sysadmin fixed server role can set a database to the EMERGENCY state.

column1: This model requires log backups. This is an addition to the full recovery model and permits high-performance bulk copy operations. This model also reduces the log space used by using minimal logging for most bulk operations. If the log is damaged or bulk-logged operations occurred since the most recent log backup, changes since that last backup must be redone. Otherwise, no work should be lost. You can recover to the end of any backup; however, point-in-time recovery is not supported.
column2: 此模型需要日志备份。这是完全恢复模型的补充，并允许进行高性能的批量复制操作。该模型还通过对大多数批量操作使用最少的日志记录来减少所使用的日志空间。如果自最近的日志备份以来日志已损坏或进行了批量记录操作，则必须重做自上次备份以来的更改。否则，任何工作都不应丢失。您可以恢复到任何备份的结尾；但是，不支持时间点恢复。

column1: This component monitor scans Windows event logs for recent events matching your defined criteria. Events are considered recent based on the age of the event as compared to the application polling frequency. If a matching event is found, the component monitor goes to down status. The component monitor eventually returns to up status as time passes. <b>You may not notice a matching event unless you create an alert to email you when the component goes down.</b>
column2: 该组件监视器扫描Windows事件日志中是否有符合您定义的条件的最新事件。与应用程序轮询频率相比，根据事件的发生时间将事件视为近期事件。如果找到匹配事件，则组件监视器将变为关闭状态。随着时间的流逝，组件监视器最终将恢复为启动状态。 <b>您可能不会注意到匹配的事件，除非您创建警报以在组件出现故障时通过电子邮件发送给您。</b>

column1: This component monitor tests the ability of an FTP server to accept an incoming session, process the user login, and then transmit the specified file to the Orion SAM server. After receiving the file, Orion SAM performs a file integrity test comparing the SHA1 checksum of the downloaded file against a previously generated checksum. column1: This component monitor uses synthetic transactions to test the abilities of a Microsoft SQL Server database. The component monitor connects to the database, performs a query, retrieves data, and then compares the data to an expected value. <br/>Statistic: Value of the first column first cell of the query result. <br/>Message: Value of the second column first cell of the query result (not required).
column2: 此组件监视器使用综合事务来测试Microsoft SQL Server数据库的功能。组件监视器连接到数据库，执行查询，检索数据，然后将数据与期望值进行比较。 <br/>统计信息：查询结果的第一列第一单元格的值。 <br/>消息：查询结果第二列第一个单元格的值（不是必需的）。

column1: Formerly known as the "WMI Performance Counter Monitor", this component monitor uses WMI communication to perform a WQL query and then return the result. Typical uses include retrieving performance data calculated by providers such as the Windows operating system and Microsoft Exchange Server. Statistic: The WQL query result.
column2: 此组件监视器以前称为“ WMI性能计数器监视器”，它使用WMI通信执行WQL查询，然后返回结果。典型用途包括检索由Windows操作系统和Microsoft Exchange Server等提供程序计算的性能数据。统计信息：WQL查询结果。

column1: Run internal and external network vulnerability scans at least quarterly and after any significant change in the network (such as new system component installations, changes in network topology, firewall rule modifications, product upgrades). Note: Multiple scan reports can be combined for the quarterly scan process to show that all systems were scanned and all applicable vulnerabilities have been addressed. Additional documentation may be required to verify non-remediated vulnerabilities are in the process of being addressed. For initial PCI DSS compliance, it is not required that four quarters of passing scans be completed if the assessor verifies 1) the most recent scan result was a passing scan, 2) the entity has documented policies and procedures requiring quarterly scanning, and 3) vulnerabilities noted in the scan results have been corrected as shown in a re-scan(s). For subsequent years after the initial PCI DSS review, four quarters of passing scans must have occurred.
column2: 在网络进行任何重大更改（例如安装新的系统组件，更改网络拓扑，修改防火墙规则，产品升级）之后，至少每季度运行一次内部和外部网络漏洞扫描。注意：可以合并多个扫描报告以进行季度扫描过程，以显示已扫描所有系统并且已解决所有适用的漏洞。可能需要其他文档来验证正在解决的不可修复的漏洞。对于最初的PCI DSS合规性，如果评估者验证1）最近的扫描结果是通过扫描，则不需要完成四分之三的通过扫描，2）实体已记录了要求每季度扫描的政策和程序，以及3）扫描结果中指出的漏洞已得到纠正，如重新扫描中所示。在最初的PCI DSS审查之后的几年中，必须进行四分之四的通过扫描。

column1: Implement physical and/or logical controls to restrict access to publicly accessible network jacks. For example, network jacks located in public areas and areas accessible to visitors could be disabled and only enabled when network access is explicitly authorized. Alternatively, processes could be implemented to ensure that visitors are escorted at all times in areas with active network jacks.

column1: Deploy a change-detection mechanism (for example, file-integrity monitoring tools) to alert personnel to unauthorized modification of critical system files, configuration files, or content files; and configure the software to perform critical file comparisons at least weekly. Note: For change-detection purposes, critical files are usually those that do not regularly change, but the modification of which could indicate a system compromise or risk of compromise. Change-detection mechanisms such as file-integrity monitoring products usually come pre-configured with critical files for the related operating system. Other critical files, such as those for custom applications, must be evaluated and defined by the entity (that is, the merchant or service provider).
column2: 部署变更检测机制（例如，文件完整性监视工具），以警告人员未经授权对关键系统文件，配置文件或内容文件进行修改；并将该软件配置为至少每周执行一次关键文件比较。注意：出于更改检测的目的，关键文件通常是那些不定期更改的文件，但是对其进行修改可能表示系统受到威胁或受到威胁的风险。诸如文件完整性监视产品之类的变化检测机制通常预先配置了相关操作系统的关键文件。其他关键文件（例如用于自定义应用程序的文件）必须由实体（即商家或服务提供商）评估和定义。

column1: Use intrusion-detection and/or intrusion-prevention techniques to detect and/or prevent intrusions into the network. Monitor all traffic at the perimeter of the cardholder data environment as well as at critical points in the cardholder data environment, and alert personnel to suspected compromises.
column2: 使用入侵检测和dor入侵防御技术来检测并防止入侵网络。在持卡人数据环境的外围以及持卡人数据环境中的关键点监视所有流量，并向工作人员发出可疑威胁的警报。

column1: If segmentation is used to isolate the CDE from other networks, perform penetration tests at least annually and after any changes to segmentation controls/methods to verify that the segmentation methods are operational and effective, and isolate all out-of-scope systems from in-scope systems.

column1: <ArrayOfAlertConditionShelve xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/SolarWinds.Orion.Core.Models.Alerting" xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"><AlertConditionShelve><AndThenTimeInterval i:nil="true"/><ChainType>Trigger</ChainType><ConditionTypeID>Core.CustomSwql</ConditionTypeID><Configuration>&lt;AlertConditionCustomSwql xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/SolarWinds.Orion.Core.Alerting.Plugins.Conditions.Swql" xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"&gt;&lt;Command&gt;INNER JOIN (SELECT disk.DataStoreID, count(disk.Snapshots.SnapshotID) AS snapCount, count(disk.DiskFileID) AS fileCount FROM Orion.VIM.DiskFiles disk  WHERE disk.Type = 'SnapshotFile'  GROUP BY disk.DataStoreID) AS d ON Datastores.DataStoreID = d.DataStoreID AND d.snapCount &amp;lt; d.fileCount WITH NOLOCK&lt;/Command&gt;&lt;/AlertConditionCustomSwql&gt;</Configuration><ConjunctionOperator>None</ConjunctionOperator><NetObjectsMinCountThreshold i:nil="true"/><ObjectType>Virtual Datastore</ObjectType><SustainTime i:nil="true"/></AlertConditionShelve></ArrayOfAlertConditionShelve>
column2: <ArrayOfAlertConditionShelve xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/SolarWinds.Orion.Core.Models.Alerting" xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"><AlertConditionShelve><AndThenTimeInterval i:nil="true"/><ChainType>Trigger</ChainType><ConditionTypeID>Core.CustomSwql</ConditionTypeID><Configuration>&lt;AlertConditionCustomSwql xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/SolarWinds.Orion.Core.Alerting.Plugins.Conditions.Swql" xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"&gt;&lt;Command&gt;INNER JOIN (SELECT disk.DataStoreID, count(disk.Snapshots.SnapshotID) AS snapCount, count(disk.DiskFileID) AS fileCount FROM Orion.VIM.DiskFiles disk  WHERE disk.Type = 'SnapshotFile'  GROUP BY disk.DataStoreID) AS d ON Datastores.DataStoreID = d.DataStoreID AND d.snapCount &amp;lt; d.fileCount WITH NOLOCK&lt;/Command&gt;&lt;/AlertConditionCustomSwql&gt;</Configuration><ConjunctionOperator>None</ConjunctionOperator><NetObjectsMinCountThreshold i:nil="true"/><ObjectType>Virtual Datastore</ObjectType><SustainTime i:nil="true"/></AlertConditionShelve></ArrayOfAlertConditionShelve>

column1: <ArrayOfAlertConditionShelve xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/SolarWinds.Orion.Core.Models.Alerting" xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"><AlertConditionShelve><AndThenTimeInterval i:nil="true"/><ChainType>Trigger</ChainType><ConditionTypeID>Core.CustomSwql</ConditionTypeID><Configuration>&lt;AlertConditionCustomSwql xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/SolarWinds.Orion.Core.Alerting.Plugins.Conditions.Swql" xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"&gt;&lt;Command&gt;INNER JOIN (SELECT h.HostID, Sum(h.VirtualMachines.HeartBeat) as sums FROM Orion.VIM.Hosts h WHERE h.VirtualMachines.PowerState = 'poweredOn' GROUP BY h.HostID) n on hosts.HostID = n.HostID and n.sums = 0&lt;/Command&gt;&lt;/AlertConditionCustomSwql&gt;</Configuration><ConjunctionOperator>None</ConjunctionOperator><NetObjectsMinCountThreshold i:nil="true"/><ObjectType>Virtual Host</ObjectType><SustainTime i:nil="true"/></AlertConditionShelve></ArrayOfAlertConditionShelve>

column1: <ArrayOfAlertConditionShelve xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/SolarWinds.Orion.Core.Models.Alerting" xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"><AlertConditionShelve><AndThenTimeInterval i:nil="true"/><ChainType>Trigger</ChainType><ConditionTypeID>Core.CustomSwql</ConditionTypeID><Configuration>&lt;AlertConditionCustomSwql xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/SolarWinds.Orion.Core.Alerting.Plugins.Conditions.Swql" xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"&gt;&lt;Command&gt;INNER JOIN  (SELECT disk.DataStoreID, Sum(disk.Size) as sums  FROM Orion.VIM.DiskFiles disk  WHERE disk.Type = 'LogFile'  GROUP BY disk.DataStoreID) d on Datastores.DataStoreID = d.DataStoreID and d.sums &amp;gt; 1073741824 WITH NOLOCK&lt;/Command&gt;&lt;/AlertConditionCustomSwql&gt;</Configuration><ConjunctionOperator>None</ConjunctionOperator><NetObjectsMinCountThreshold i:nil="true"/><ObjectType>Virtual Datastore</ObjectType><SustainTime i:nil="true"/></AlertConditionShelve></ArrayOfAlertConditionShelve>

column1: <ArrayOfAlertConditionShelve xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/SolarWinds.Orion.Core.Models.Alerting" xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"><AlertConditionShelve><AndThenTimeInterval i:nil="true"/><ChainType>Trigger</ChainType><ConditionTypeID>Core.CustomSwql</ConditionTypeID><Configuration>&lt;AlertConditionCustomSwql xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/SolarWinds.Orion.Core.Alerting.Plugins.Conditions.Swql" xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"&gt;&lt;Command&gt;INNER JOIN  (SELECT DISTINCT vm.VirtualMachineID   FROM Orion.VIM.VirtualMachines vm  WHERE (vm.TotalStorageSizeUsed-(vm.VolumeSummaryCapacity - vm.VolumeSummaryFreeSpace)&amp;gt;1073741824) and vm.VirtualDisks.ThinProvisioned=true and vm.VolumeSummaryCapacity&amp;lt;&amp;gt;0)  v on VirtualMachines.VirtualMachineID = v.VirtualMachineID &lt;/Command&gt;&lt;/AlertConditionCustomSwql&gt;</Configuration><ConjunctionOperator>None</ConjunctionOperator><NetObjectsMinCountThreshold i:nil="true"/><ObjectType>Virtual Machine</ObjectType><SustainTime i:nil="true"/></AlertConditionShelve></ArrayOfAlertConditionShelve>

column1: <ArrayOfAlertConditionShelve xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/SolarWinds.Orion.Core.Models.Alerting" xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"><AlertConditionShelve><AndThenTimeInterval i:nil="true"/><ChainType>Trigger</ChainType><ConditionTypeID>Core.CustomSwql</ConditionTypeID><Configuration>&lt;AlertConditionCustomSwql xmlns="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/SolarWinds.Orion.Core.Alerting.Plugins.Conditions.Swql" xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"&gt;&lt;Command&gt;where DayDiff(virtualmachines.VirtualDiskDateModified, getdate())&amp;gt;30 and (virtualmachines.SnapshotSummaryCount=0 or DayDiff( virtualmachines.SnapshotDateModified, getdate())&amp;gt;30)&lt;/Command&gt;&lt;/AlertConditionCustomSwql&gt;</Configuration><ConjunctionOperator>None</ConjunctionOperator><NetObjectsMinCountThreshold i:nil="true"/><ObjectType>Virtual Machine</ObjectType><SustainTime i:nil="true"/></AlertConditionShelve></ArrayOfAlertConditionShelve>

column2: 向环境中添加其他VM的影响

column1: Recommended value is {{::vm.utilizationPeriodLimits.recommended}} days or more.
The planner will not perform a projection. It will just report on the current (or simulated) state of the environment.

模拟添加额外的虚拟机

column1: When estimating the footprint of VMs, the planner can use several different models.
column2: 在估算VM的占用空间时，计划者可以使用几种不同的模型。

column1: Aggregated data of VM workload usages in the cluster.
column2: 群集中VM工作负载使用情况的汇总数据。

column1: CPU core count value must be {0} or higher.
column2: CPU核心计数值必须为{0}或更高。

column1: Use the 95th percentile of VM resource usage measurements. This model balances VM performance and efficient resource allocation.
column2: 使用VM资源使用率测量值的95％。该模型平衡了VM性能和有效的资源分配。

column1: The planner will examine usage trends on your real resources to predict future usage.
column2: 计划者将检查您实际资源上的使用趋势，以预测将来的使用情况。

column1: Examine the current state of one of your clusters. Predict when future capacity problems are likely to occur.
column2: 检查您的群集之一的当前状态。预测将来可能出现的容量问题。

column1: View the impact of adding more host computers to one of your clusters.
column2: 查看将更多主机计算机添加到一个群集中的影响。

column1: CPU core count value cannot exceed {0}.

column2: 特定于事件的详细信息

column1: Aggregated data of host resources in the cluster.
column2: 集群中主机资源的聚合数据。

column1: The planner has everything it needs to estimate your future usage.
